{
  "texts": [
    "Distribution of KiDZ spectroscopic redshift estimates in RA-z space.",
    "Sources in orange indicate estimates that were available for previous KiDS analyses, and sources in cyan show new estimates added here.",
    "Differences between photo-z point-estimates produced by BPZ in PHOTOPIPE computed without the second pass i-band ('9-band') and with the second pass i-band ('10-band'), using a full simulated KiDS wide-field sample described in van denBusch et al. (2020).",
    "Metrics here are not directly comparable to Fig.25due to this sample being simulated, having a different redshift baseline, and representing a full wide-field sample (unmatched to spectroscopy).",
    "Therefore, only relative differences between the nine-and ten-band cases are relevant."
  ]
}